manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: HELLY HANSEN - ALIVE SINCE 1877 From our home in Norway, Helly Hansen has been making professional grade gear to help people stay and feel alive for more than 140 years. It all started in 1877 when sea captain Helly Juell Hansen found a better way to stay protected from the harsh Norwegian elements. Soon thereafter, Captain Hansen and his wife Margrethe launched a business producing waterproof oilskin jackets, trousers, sou’westers and tarpaulins made from coarse linen soaked in linseed oil – and the legend was born! Helly Hansen gear is worn and trusted by professionals on oceans, mountains and worksites. As the #1 apparel brand for Ski Professionals, you’ll find HH at more than 200 ski resort and guiding operations around the world, and worn by more than 55,000 ski professionals. Our sailing gear is worn by world-class sailors across all five oceans, and we’re proud to partner with and participate in some of the sport’s most iconic regattas and sailing associations. As a leading Scandinavian workwear brand, you’ll see us at work-sites where performance, protection and safety matter most. We continue to support Captain Hansen’s legacy through a long list of first-to-market innovations developed through insights from those working and recreating in the world’s harshest environments.

MOUNTAIN Since 1877 Helly Hansen has worked with professionals in Norway to create gear so people can stay and feel alive in the beautiful but harsh Scandinavian outdoors.The insights drawn from outdoor professionals, their knowledge and experience have been instrumental in creating our mountain line of today. Based on this knowledge we aim to continuously redefine the way we design, develop and use outdoor gear to experience and preserve the outdoors for generations to come.

SAILING As the recognized global leader in sailing, our gear is worn by world-class sailors across all five oceans on anything from dinghies to 100ft foiling catamarans. In the Spring of 2020 we take another big leap and partner with the professionals on the American Magic team to change, shape and create the future technologies of sailing and win the 36th America’s Cup.

SKI Since 1877 Helly Hansen has been delivering product solutions for those working in the outdoors. We believe that by focusing on the needs of the outdoor professional that we will exceed the needs of the recreational user and improve both of their experiences outdoors. Working with over 55,000 professionals in the ski industry, we utilize their feedback and experience to drive our product development process to consistently deliver products that meet the demands of the professional environment.

HELLY HANSEN WORKWEAR Helly Hansen is the brand trusted by professionals. Since 1877 they have created professional grade gear to help people stay and feel alive. Helly Hansen's workwear collection is built to make sure you get the job done. Today of course Helly Hansen is synonymous with high quality and reliability, the tool of choice for the serious tradesman and used globally as survival and rescue gear by emergency services including the Royal National Lifeboat Institution, the world's oldest lifeboat service.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best all in one jacket for my need
reviews.reviewText: I was on the hunt for a jacket which serves me purpose on rainy and cold days. Living in washinton most of rhe days are rainy and cold. This is the best purchase I did to solve my standings on cold and rainy days during my sons soccer games.The double insulation keeps you warm. Have been in rain on multiple occasions and no leaks so far. More options for storage. More option on functionality on how you want to wear it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This coat fits well and kept me warm enough this morning in 13 degree temperatures with a moderate wind. I wasn’t toasty warm, but I wasn’t cold either. I wore a tank with a fleece shirt over it under the coat and am a big cold baby, so it did really well. The length is fabulous! My legs were warm! I have a warmer Canada goose jacket, but my legs and butt are always cold - with this coat, they were finally warm and I think that helped keep my feet warmer. I can’t wait to try it out in the spring rains.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars All I could ask for in a winter coat.
reviews.reviewText: I'll start with sizing. Normally I take a large so thats what I tried first. Was fine if my arms were down, but if I put my arms out straight forward like I was reaching for something, the cuffs of the sleeves would be at the middle of my forearms. The extra large version was what I needed.So more generally speaking, this is a very utilitarian jacket. Lots of pockets, very waterproof, suprisingly warm, and even kinda heavy for what it is (which is good!). It is a little awkward to get the zipper started, but I think any long coat is like this, and the added warmth is worth it.I would recommend this to anyone. FYI, I live in central lower peninsula of Michigan and its good enough with just a t-shirt under it most days. Just go with a size larger than you normally do.

As a commercial fisher and now retired I have worn Helly Hanson rain gear for almost 50 years with good result s, long lasting and tough so when I needed a semi dress rain coat I choos ethics coat and so far it has been great , I even had a compliment that I looked very Swish in it . My only concern is that it is a little tight for a XL and shortly after receiving it the coat hanger came apart on the coat though the liner still has one. overall a good coat and received it just before we went into two weeks of Artic outflow combined with Snow and heavy freezing.

reviews.reviewTitle: Skeptical at first, convinced like never before
reviews.reviewText: I always read the reviews on everything I buy. I tried to buy many different winter coats this year (3) and none of them made the job. I like when the coat is sticking to the body but I also love when it has style (since I am an artist). This coat is just the perfect fit for me in all terms. Beautiful design, long length, perfectly fitting my body, warm. Now the only thing to see is if it will stay in good shape through the next winters.

Very quick, very easy review….BUY IT!!!!This us an awesome winter coat. Love the design with the patches, the fact it has a zip out lining and the length is nice and long.VERY WARM!! I live in Canada where today it’s -22*F .. jacket kept me warm no problem.Highly recommend this jacket. ZERO complaints at all ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
